WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.000
This is the story of Hapu.

00:04.000 --> 00:10.000
He lives in ancient Egypt at the time of Queen Cleopatra.

00:10.000 --> 00:15.000
His father, back, has a small factory.

00:15.000 --> 00:19.000
He makes gold tables and chairs.

00:19.000 --> 00:22.000
Hapu helps him.

00:22.000 --> 00:25.000
He is a fireboy.

00:25.000 --> 00:30.000
Every day, he pushes a long handle up and down.

00:30.000 --> 00:34.000
The work is hot, and it's very hard.

00:34.000 --> 00:38.000
But what can he and his father do?

00:38.000 --> 00:41.000
They are poor people.

00:41.000 --> 00:44.000
They need to make money.

00:44.000 --> 00:49.000
Every evening, they sit beside the Nile.

00:49.000 --> 00:53.000
Back talks to his son about the factory.

00:53.000 --> 00:57.000
Tomorrow's work, everything.

00:57.000 --> 01:02.000
One day, we're going to be very rich, he tells Hapu.

01:02.000 --> 01:04.000
Are we?

01:04.000 --> 01:09.000
The fireboy looks into his father's tired eyes.

01:09.000 --> 01:11.000
Yes.

01:11.000 --> 01:13.000
Back smiles.

01:13.000 --> 01:17.000
I don't know how, and I don't know when.

01:17.000 --> 01:19.000
But we are.

01:19.000 --> 01:22.000
Then he stands up.

01:22.000 --> 01:24.000
Come on, he says.

01:24.000 --> 01:26.000
It's late.

01:26.000 --> 01:30.000
Let's go home.

01:30.000 --> 01:37.000
Three days later, Hapu and back are making a table.

01:37.000 --> 01:40.000
It's very hot in the room.

01:40.000 --> 01:44.000
Suddenly, back stops work.

01:44.000 --> 01:46.000
What is it, father?

01:46.000 --> 01:50.000
Hapu asks, is something wrong?

01:50.000 --> 01:52.000
I don't know.

01:52.000 --> 01:54.000
Back answers.

01:54.000 --> 01:57.000
He closes his eyes.

01:57.000 --> 01:59.000
It's my head.

01:59.000 --> 02:02.000
I can't.

02:02.000 --> 02:07.000
And then, he falls on the ground.

02:07.000 --> 02:09.000
Father?

02:09.000 --> 02:14.000
Hapu runs to back and puts one hand under his head.

02:14.000 --> 02:19.000
Father, are you all right?

02:19.000 --> 02:23.000
The next day, back stays in bed.

02:23.000 --> 02:25.000
I'm sorry, Hapu.

02:25.000 --> 02:29.000
He says, I want to work, but I can't.

02:29.000 --> 02:32.000
I'm ill.

02:32.000 --> 02:35.000
Hapu is very sad.

02:35.000 --> 02:39.000
Father works too hard, he thinks.

02:39.000 --> 02:41.000
That's why he's ill.

02:41.000 --> 02:44.000
We need more money.

02:44.000 --> 02:47.000
But what can I do?

02:47.000 --> 02:51.000
Then, he has an idea.

02:51.000 --> 02:54.000
Of course, he thinks.

02:54.000 --> 02:59.000
I must make something for somebody very rich.

02:59.000 --> 03:03.000
Somebody like the queen.

03:03.000 --> 03:07.000
Back is ill for two weeks.

03:07.000 --> 03:13.000
In that time, Hapu makes a lot of tables and chairs.

03:13.000 --> 03:17.000
But not only tables and chairs.

03:17.000 --> 03:21.000
He makes a gold necklace too.

03:21.000 --> 03:25.000
There, he thinks late one night.

03:25.000 --> 03:27.000
It's ready.

03:27.000 --> 03:30.000
He smiles.

03:30.000 --> 03:33.000
The necklace is very beautiful.

03:33.000 --> 03:38.000
Queen Cleopatra is going to like this, Hapu thinks.

03:38.000 --> 03:42.000
She's going to pay a lot of money for it too.

03:42.000 --> 03:45.000
I know she is.

03:45.000 --> 03:50.000
The next morning, he goes to Cleopatra's palace.

03:50.000 --> 03:54.000
The necklace is in a bag under his shirt.

03:54.000 --> 03:59.000
What do you want asks a palace guard?

03:59.000 --> 04:02.000
There are two guards.

04:02.000 --> 04:06.000
Each one has a sword.

04:06.000 --> 04:11.000
I want to see the queen, Hapu answers.

04:11.000 --> 04:13.000
Both guards laugh.

04:13.000 --> 04:15.000
Go home boy.

04:15.000 --> 04:17.000
Says one of them.

04:17.000 --> 04:21.000
Queen Cleopatra doesn't see people like you.

04:21.000 --> 04:25.000
Hapu is very unhappy.

04:25.000 --> 04:27.000
What do I do now?

04:27.000 --> 04:29.000
He thinks.

04:29.000 --> 04:34.000
He leaves the palace and begins to walk home.

04:34.000 --> 04:39.000
But ten minutes later, he passes two men in the market.

04:39.000 --> 04:45.000
Cleopatra's women are coming here tomorrow morning, says one.

04:45.000 --> 04:48.000
They're arriving very early.

04:48.000 --> 04:53.000
They want to buy lots of new clothes for her.

04:53.000 --> 04:58.000
That's very good news, Hapu thinks.

04:58.000 --> 05:03.000
The next day, the fire boy gets up very early.

05:03.000 --> 05:07.000
He makes a cup of sweet tea for back.

05:07.000 --> 05:10.000
Then he goes to the market.

05:10.000 --> 05:16.000
I can give the necklace to Cleopatra's women, he thinks.

05:16.000 --> 05:20.000
They can give it to the queen for me.

05:20.000 --> 05:24.000
He waits and waits.

05:24.000 --> 05:28.000
For a long time, nothing happens.

05:28.000 --> 05:33.000
Then, music starts to play.

05:33.000 --> 05:39.000
A moment later, Hapu sees a long line of people.

05:39.000 --> 05:43.000
They are coming from the palace.

05:48.000 --> 05:53.000
Four men are carrying a very beautiful chair.

05:53.000 --> 05:57.000
A woman is sitting in it.

05:57.000 --> 06:01.000
Hapu puts one hand across his eyes.

06:01.000 --> 06:05.000
It's the queen, he thinks.

06:05.000 --> 06:09.000
She's coming too.

06:09.000 --> 06:14.000
A minute later, Cleopatra arrives.

06:14.000 --> 06:19.000
Suddenly, everyone is very quiet.

06:19.000 --> 06:25.000
Then, Hapu thinks, this is the moment.

06:25.000 --> 06:30.000
He runs in front of Cleopatra's chair.

06:30.000 --> 06:35.000
Stop, he says. Please stop.

06:35.000 --> 06:38.000
The queen looks at him.

06:38.000 --> 06:42.000
What do you want? She asks.

06:42.000 --> 06:47.000
Hapu gives her the necklace.

06:47.000 --> 06:50.000
Is this really your work?

06:50.000 --> 06:53.000
Asked Cleopatra?

06:53.000 --> 06:58.000
Yes, yes it is. Hapu answers.

06:58.000 --> 07:01.000
Gods, says Cleopatra.

07:01.000 --> 07:05.000
Give this boy some money.

07:05.000 --> 07:09.000
She holds the necklace in her hands.

07:09.000 --> 07:13.000
This is beautiful, she says.

07:13.000 --> 07:16.000
Then, she leads.

07:16.000 --> 07:19.000
Hapu runs home.

07:19.000 --> 07:23.000
He is very, very happy.

07:23.000 --> 07:26.000
That isn't bad.

07:26.000 --> 07:30.000
Look, Hapu says.

07:30.000 --> 07:36.000
He shows the money from Cleopatra's necklace to his father.

07:36.000 --> 07:39.000
But howl?

07:39.000 --> 07:44.000
Buck closes his eyes, then opens them again.

07:44.000 --> 07:49.000
I don't understand, he says.

07:49.000 --> 07:52.000
Hapu smiles.

07:52.000 --> 07:58.000
He sits down and tells his father everything.

07:58.000 --> 08:02.000
At the end of the story, Buck says,

08:02.000 --> 08:05.000
you're a good son, Hapu.

08:05.000 --> 08:08.000
Thank you.

08:08.000 --> 08:13.000
That night, Hapu looks up at the stars.

08:13.000 --> 08:19.000
Now, I can pay for a doctor to visit father, he thinks.

08:19.000 --> 08:23.000
Then, after father is strong again,

08:23.000 --> 08:27.000
but at that moment, he stops.

08:27.000 --> 08:33.000
One of Cleopatra's gods is standing in front of him.

08:33.000 --> 08:36.000
He has a big sword.

08:36.000 --> 08:40.000
Are you Hapu, son of Buck?

08:40.000 --> 08:42.000
He asks.

08:42.000 --> 08:45.000
Hapu looks at him.

08:45.000 --> 08:48.000
Yes. Yes, I am.

08:48.000 --> 08:50.000
He answers.

08:50.000 --> 08:54.000
Come with me, says the god.

08:54.000 --> 08:58.000
Queen Cleopatra likes your work.

08:58.000 --> 09:03.000
She wants to give you a job at the palace.

09:03.000 --> 09:07.000
But I have a job, Hapu says.

09:07.000 --> 09:10.000
I work with my father.

09:10.000 --> 09:12.000
I can't leave him.

09:12.000 --> 09:15.000
You don't understand.

09:15.000 --> 09:21.000
No. You don't understand, the god says.

09:21.000 --> 09:27.000
When the queen gives you a job, you take it.

09:27.000 --> 09:30.000
He puts one hand on his sword.

09:30.000 --> 09:36.000
Now, go and say goodbye to your father.

09:36.000 --> 09:41.000
At the palace, Cleopatra talks to Hapu.

09:41.000 --> 09:44.000
She is wearing his necklace.

09:44.000 --> 09:52.000
I want you to live here and make lots of beautiful things for me, she says.

09:52.000 --> 09:57.000
Thank you, queen of the Nile, Hapu says.

09:57.000 --> 09:59.000
But...

09:59.000 --> 10:03.000
But the queen looks at Hapu.

10:03.000 --> 10:07.000
But I can't live here.

10:07.000 --> 10:12.000
You see, my father is very ill and...

10:12.000 --> 10:16.000
Hapu tells the queen everything.

10:16.000 --> 10:23.000
At the end of Hapu's story, Cleopatra looks at him.

10:23.000 --> 10:26.000
All right, she says.

10:26.000 --> 10:29.000
You can go home to your father.

10:29.000 --> 10:31.000
But...

10:31.000 --> 10:34.000
But asks Hapu.

10:34.000 --> 10:40.000
But from today, the two of you work only for me.

10:40.000 --> 10:43.000
Do you understand?

10:43.000 --> 10:47.000
Oh, yes, Hapu smiles.

10:47.000 --> 10:50.000
He is very happy.

10:50.000 --> 10:59.000
Now, he and his father can make lots of beautiful things and be rich.

10:59.000 --> 11:03.000
Yes, I understand.

